"v.谈话；a.逆向的n.相反的事物 【英】 adj. 逆向的(opposite) v. 交谈(思想、看法或感情); adj (在位置、次序或行为上)反向的 = contrary = opposite; n 对立物 【例】I hold the converse opinion 我持反对意见. 【记】con + verse 一起对诗→对话 【相关】university 综合性大学 converse (v.)  ""to communicate (with),"" 1590s; earlier ""to move about, live, dwell"" (mid-14c.), from Old French converser ""to talk"" (12c.), from Latin conversari (see conversation). Related: Conversed; conversing. converse (adj.)  ""exact opposite,"" 1560s, from Latin conversus ""turn around,"" past participle of convertere ""to turn about"" (see convert). Originally mathematical. The noun is attested from 1550s in mathematics. Related: Conversely."
